

[[toc]]
+ Root element input
[[# input]]
++++* Attributes:
+++++* scratchpath

[[# scratchpath]]This is the path to scratch space where the eigenvector file EIGVEC.OUT will be written. If the local directory is accessed via a network then scrpath can be set to a directory on

**type:** xs:anyURI **use:** optional 
+++++* id

[[# id]]The id is a unique identifier in an input set. If the input element is part of an input set the id must be set.

**type:** xs:ID 
+++++* depends

[[# depends]]the depends attribute can be used to specify a dependence from another simulation in the same input set.

**type:** xs:IDREFS 

+ structure element
[[# structure]]The structure element contains all structural information such as atoms atom positions and symmetries.
++++* Attributes:
+++++* speciespath

[[# speciespath]]gives the path to the directory containing the species files

**type:** xs:anyURI **use:** required 
+++++* molecule

[[# molecule]]true if the system is an isolated molecule

**type:** xs:boolean **default-value:** false 
+++++* epslat

[[# epslat]]vectors with lengths less than this are considered zero

**type:** xs:double **default-value:** 1e-6 
+++++* autormt

[[# autormt]]

**type:** xs:boolean 
+++++* vacuum

[[# vacuum]]

**type:** xs:double 
+++++* lradstp

[[# lradstp]]Some muffn-tin functions (such as the density) are calculated on a coarse radial mesh and then interpolated onto a fine mesh. This is done for the sake of efficiency. lradstp defines the step size in going from the fine to the coarse radial mesh. If it is too large, loss of precision may occur.

**type:** xs:integer **default-value:** 4 

++ crystal element
[[# crystal]]defines the unit cell of the simulation
++++* Attributes:
+++++* scale

[[# scale]]gives a scaling factor for the unit cell. it scales the lattice vectors. This is useful for varying the volume.

**type:** xs:double **default-value:** 1 
+++++* stretch

[[# stretch]]separate scaling for each lattice vector 1 1 1 is no scaling

**type:** vect3d **default-value:** 1.0   1.0  1.0  
+++++* primcell

[[# primcell]]Allows the primitive unit cell to be determined automatically from the conventional cell. This is done by searching for lattice vectors among all those which connect atomic sites, and using the three shortest which produce a unit cell with non-zero volume.

**type:** xs:boolean **default-value:** false 

+++ basevect element
[[# basevect]]basevectors or lattice vectors in Bohr
++ species element
[[# species]]for each atom type (species) a species element is defined containing all the atom positions
++++* Attributes:
+++++* chemicalSymbol

[[# chemicalSymbol]]The species abrevation is looked up in the species directory specified by the species path

**type:** xs:string **use:** required 
+++++* speciesfile

[[# speciesfile]]not implemented but may be used to specify a file for custom species definition

**type:** xs:anyURI **default-value:**  

+++ atom element
[[# atom]]atomic position in lattice coordinates for atom
